		<title>Vapi Raises $50M to Expand Enterprise Voice AI</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/vapi-raises-50m-to-expand-enterprise-voice-ai/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 19:22:02 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=201105</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Vapi has raised $50 million in Series B funding. The funding round marks a transition in the AI industry from basic text-based chatbots to high-fidelity, low-latency voice interactions targeted at</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/vapi-raises-50m-to-expand-enterprise-voice-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal">Vapi Raises $50M to Expand Enterprise Voice AI</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://vapi.ai/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Vapi </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has raised $50 million in Series B </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/elliptic-raises-120m-from-nasdaq-ventures-and-deutsche-bank/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. The funding round marks a transition in the AI industry from basic text-based chatbots to high-fidelity, low-latency voice interactions targeted at the largest enterprises in the world. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding round was led by Peak XV Partners (formerly Sequoia India &amp; Southeast Asia) with a large proportion led by M12 (Microsoft Venture Fund), Kleiner Perkins &amp; Bessemer Venture Partners.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This fresh injection of capital raises its funding to $72m. The recent round comes after an incredible 12 months for the company, which has seen tenfold growth of yearly recurring revenue (ARR).</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Reaching the One Billion Call Milestone</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Vapi’s rise has been fuelled by a massive surge in demand from industries that rely heavily on phone-based communication, such as healthcare, financial services, and retail. Alongside the funding news, the company revealed it has now powered over one billion calls through its platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Unlike traditional Interactive Voice Response (IVR) systems, which often frustrate customers with rigid &#8220;Press 1 for sales&#8221; menus, Vapi&#8217;s platform allows developers to build voice agents that listen, understand context, and respond with human-like latency.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201115" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201115" class="size-large wp-image-201115" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/vapi-1024x291.png" alt="vapi logo" width="1024" height="291" /><p id="caption-attachment-201115" class="wp-caption-text">Source: vapi</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;When a customer calls a business, they aren&#8217;t looking for another channel; they are looking for an outcome,&#8221; said Jordan Dearsley, co-founder of Vapi. &#8220;Most phone experiences run on rigid scripts that can&#8217;t adapt. We built Vapi to make the voice channel extraordinary by allowing agents to have real conversations at scale.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/elliptic-raises-120m-from-nasdaq-ventures-and-deutsche-bank/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Elliptic Raises $120M From Nasdaq Ventures and Deutsche Bank</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Transforming the Enterprise Support Stack</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform’s success is already visible within major organizations. Amazon Ring, a key Vapi customer, recently moved 100% of its inbound support volume to the platform. According to Jason Mitura, VP of Software Development at Amazon Ring, the transition from zero to full production took just two weeks and resulted in improved customer satisfaction (CSAT) scores.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Vapi’s &#8220;bottom-up&#8221; developer-first approach has earned it comparisons to companies like Zapier and Twilio. By providing an API-first infrastructure, Vapi abstracts away the complexities of telephony, allowing engineers to focus on the conversation logic rather than the underlying telecommunications hardware.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Goals: Governance and Reliability</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Vapi is committing this new $50 million in capital to enterprise governance and predictability. As AI agents take over real high-stakes workflows like insurance claims or medical triage, reliability becomes king.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is investing heavily in:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Predictable Latency:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Keeping responses reliably within the 500ms to 800ms range for a natural conversation.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Advanced Monitoring:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Solutions that treat every call to your AI as a production workload and provide deep analytics and human-in-the-loop escalation paths.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Global Infrastructure:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Expanding its server footprint to support multinational corporations requiring localised, low-latency voice services.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;In ten years, it’s likely most calls will not have a human behind the phone,&#8221; said Arnav Sahu, partner at Peak XV. &#8220;Vapi has the potential to be the defining platform for this entire revolution.&#8221;</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/vapi-raises-50m-to-expand-enterprise-voice-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal">Vapi Raises $50M to Expand Enterprise Voice AI</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
