					<description><![CDATA[<p>Elliptic, a world-renowned information service provider for digital asset risk management and blockchain analytics, announced that it has successfully closed a Series D funding of $120 million. The round was</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/elliptic-raises-120m-from-nasdaq-ventures-and-deutsche-bank/" data-wpel-link="internal">Elliptic Raises $120M From Nasdaq Ventures and Deutsche Bank</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.elliptic.co/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Elliptic</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, a world-renowned information service provider for digital asset risk management and blockchain analytics, announced that it has successfully closed a Series D </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/adfin-raises-18m-to-automate-finance-workflows/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">of $120 million. The round was led by One Peak Partners with significant investments from Nasdaq Ventures, Deutsche Bank, and the British Business Bank, as well as a follow-on investment from current investors, including JPMorgan Chase.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This latest round of capital, valuing the London-based company at nearly $670 million, marks a major milestone towards the establishment of the digital asset ecosystem. The industry is increasingly working alongside traditional financial institutions using blockchain technology.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling Institutional-Grade Infrastructure</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Elliptic has been developing a proprietary data engine that tracks over 65 blockchains over the last ten years. Today, it has more than 700 customers, including many top banks, fintechs, and government agencies worldwide. As 2/3 of global crypto trading activity flows through exchanges, Elliptic services are now the de facto industry standard for on-chain transparency.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201094" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201094" class="size-full wp-image-201094" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/elliptic-logo-black.jpg" alt="elliptic logo" width="480" height="360" /><p id="caption-attachment-201094" class="wp-caption-text">Source: elliptic</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new funding will be used to fund two major strategic initiatives: the growth of Elliptic&#8217;s AI-native compliance tools and the development of the company&#8217;s &#8216;agentic&#8217; product roadmap. Elliptic plans to use autonomous AI agents to address the highly manual, repetitive nature of transaction screening and investigation, enabling compliance officers at large financial institutions to act more as strategic decision-makers and less as triage operators of billions of pieces of data weekly.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/adfin-raises-18m-to-automate-finance-workflows/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Adfin Raises $18M to Automate Finance Workflows</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Rise of Stablecoins and Tokenized Assets</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The rapid growth of the stablecoin and tokenized assets markets is a key factor in this rising investment. When the global value of stablecoin transacting in 2025 is estimated at $33 trillion, stablecoins will have gone from a fringe element of finance to a dominant feature of its infrastructure. Central banks and private players both bring to bear a growing number of tokenized securities and blockchain-based settlement arrangements. Real-time insights across public and private ledgers have hit a tipping point.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The involvement of Nasdaq Ventures and Deutsche Bank sends a message that is part of the continuing maturation of the industry. Their investment indicates that these financial institutions are no longer taking a hands-off approach but are willing to put their money down to fund the regulated, compliant infrastructure necessary to push digital assets to the global stage. An investment, no less, that assumes the crypto economy&#8217;s future viability depends on an institutional risk infrastructure.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Global Regulatory Alignment</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding is also happening around the time of expanded major oversight, for instance, the Markets in Crypto-Assets (MiCA) regulation in Europe. These regulations require greater compliance from providers, who will now have to deploy sophisticated analytics to avoid inadvertently supporting illicit finance and contravening global sanctions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This overarching insight delivered by Elliptic, tracking funds across various blockchains and exposing related parties to blacklist addresses or fraud, continues to be its strongest competitive advantage. With $120 million in new capital, Elliptic is well equipped to run the next step in digital asset decisioning, where compliance is not just a regulatory paper chase but an integrated, automated part of the global financial plumbing.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/elliptic-raises-120m-from-nasdaq-ventures-and-deutsche-bank/" data-wpel-link="internal">Elliptic Raises $120M From Nasdaq Ventures and Deutsche Bank</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
