		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 15:00:17 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=201089</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Isomorphic Labs, a startup that had a declaration of backing from Google DeepMind, has raised $2.1 billion in a Series B funding round. The large investment, which is one of</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/isomorphic-labs-raises-2-1b-for-ai-drug-discovery/" data-wpel-link="internal">Isomorphic Labs Raises $2.1B for AI Drug Discovery</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.isomorphiclabs.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Isomorphic Labs</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, a startup that had a declaration of backing from Google DeepMind, has raised $2.1 billion in a Series B </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/adfin-raises-18m-to-automate-finance-workflows/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. The large investment, which is one of the biggest rounds ever in the &#8220;AI bio&#8221; space, highlights the increasing belief that computer models are ready to turn from predicting protein structures to the mass production of life-saving drugs.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding round was led by Thrive Capital, which previously spearheaded the company’s initial external financing. The round saw significant participation from Isomorphic’s parent company, Alphabet, alongside its venture arm GV and growth fund CapitalG. Notably, the round also attracted a diverse group of new global investors, including MGX, Temasek, and the UK Sovereign AI Fund, bringing the company’s total funding to approximately $2.6 billion.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">From Theory to Engineering</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Established as a standalone research company in late 2021 after being spun out from Google DeepMind, Isomorphic Labs aims to reinvent drug discovery as an end-to-end engineering problem. Led by Sir Demis Hassabis (also CEO of Google AI), Isomorphic has built an Isomorphic AI Drug Design Engine (IsoDDE) on the foundations of the Nobel Prize-winning AlphaFold1.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201090" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201090" class="size-large wp-image-201090" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Person-in-the-lab-1024x642.jpg" alt="Person in the lab" width="1024" height="642" /><p id="caption-attachment-201090" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Though the first AlphaFold was a pioneer by providing 3D protein structure predictions, the current and more advanced models from Isomorphic intend to do a lot more. These systems model the complex physical and chemical interactions between potential drug molecules and their biological targets. The goal is to predict not just what a protein looks like but also how it will behave when introduced to a specific synthetic compound, at a level of precision and speed that traditional lab-based &#8220;trial and error&#8221; cannot match.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/adfin-raises-18m-to-automate-finance-workflows/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Adfin Raises $18M to Automate Finance Workflows</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Clinical Ambitions and Global Expansion</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The fresh cash is set to be allocated for a significant scaling drive. Isomorphic intends to intensify its internal pipeline of therapeutic programs, forcing them at a quick pace toward Phase I clinical trials. Despite the fact that no human patient has been dosed so far, it&#8217;s reasonable to think 2026 funding indicates a shift toward the clinical stage.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Meanwhile, though its own internal pipeline is relatively weak, the firm is exploring the field of high-profile strategic alliances and is in the process of tripling it. IsoMorph has already negotiated multi-billion-dollar R&amp;D partnerships with big pharma players such as Eli Lilly, Novartis and, notably, J&amp;J. These external mega-pacts (on top of its lucrative in-house research program) help provide the firm with both vast amounts of data and an industry Q.C. insider, while giving IsoDDE a proving ground in situations from cancer to immune disorders.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Transatlantic Talent War</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Importantly, the funds will also enable a large increase in headcount. Isomorphic is hiring out of their London and US hubs, looking for a hard-to-find combination: machine learning researchers who speak biology and medicinal chemists who are happy in a code-first environment.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The UK Sovereign AI Fund&#8217;s decision to become a large investor in the initial offering underscores Isomorphic&#8217;s centrality to the UK technology industry. The UK&#8217;s choice to base one of the world&#8217;s most valuable AI companies in London is in line with the country&#8217;s ultimate goal of cementing its competitiveness as a major global force in the so-called &#8220;Life Sciences 2.0&#8221; era.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/isomorphic-labs-raises-2-1b-for-ai-drug-discovery/" data-wpel-link="internal">Isomorphic Labs Raises $2.1B for AI Drug Discovery</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
