					<description><![CDATA[<p>Paymentology has raised a massive $175 million investment round. This is one of the largest funds to be injected into the payment infrastructure industry all year, and suggests a clear</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/paymentology-raises-175m-to-expand-global-payments/" data-wpel-link="internal">Paymentology Raises $175M to Expand Global Payments</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.paymentology.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Paymentology </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has raised a massive $175 million </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/ripple-prime-secures-200m-debt-deal-from-neuberger/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">investment </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. This is one of the largest funds to be injected into the payment infrastructure industry all year, and suggests a clear move away from the old systems, which hinder innovation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round was led by both the well-known private equity fund Apis Partners, which focuses on financial infrastructure, and Pan-European Aspirity Partners, which was making Paymentology the first investment of its fledgling fund.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This partnership introduces not just capital but also a strong network of sector expertise designed to grow Paymentology&#8217;s coverage across the Middle East, Latin America, Africa, and Asia Pacific.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the Legacy Problem</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Although the total global payments market size will reach $49 trillion by the end of 2026, many have yet to move on from longstanding, inflexible legacy infrastructure. This can be a big impediment to the ability of banks and fintechs to deploy new products swiftly, process trillions of dollars of real-time transactions, or maintain international operations without significant technical modifications.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201086" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201086" class="size-large wp-image-201086" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Paymentology-1536x346-1-1024x231.jpeg" alt="Paymentology logo" width="1024" height="231" /><p id="caption-attachment-201086" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Paymentology</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Paymentology’s cloud-native platform is designed to be the antidote to this friction. By offering a highly configurable architecture, the company allows digital banks, telcos, and established financial institutions to launch and manage card programs with unprecedented speed.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Legacy infrastructure continues to be the single biggest constraint on innovation in the issuing layer,&#8221; said Jeff Parker, CEO of Paymentology. &#8220;We’ve built a platform that gives our clients the control and flexibility they need to compete. This investment is a massive endorsement of that vision.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/ripple-prime-secures-200m-debt-deal-from-neuberger/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Ripple Prime Secures $200M Debt Deal from Neuberger</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Explosive Growth and Strategic Evolution</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding comes in the wake of hypergrowth for the British company. During FY2025, Paymentology experienced a 117% YoY spike in new sales as well as a 65% increase in transaction volumes. Paymentology, already a service provider of card programs across around 70+ countries for the likes of M-Pesa (by Safaricom), Wio Bank, and GoTyme, works with global giants.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Despite having its core business of issuer processing, Paymentology intends to use the $175 million to grow into high-growth adjacent markets, such as the following:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Stablecoins and Digital Assets:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Integrating blockchain-linked card programmes.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Tokenisation:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Enhancing security for mobile and digital wallets.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>AI-Driven Services:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Utilising real-time data to provide predictive analytics for fraud prevention and customer spending patterns.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A New Standard for Financial Inclusion</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Beyond technology, the investment emphasises a social mandate. By lowering the cost and technical barriers to issuing cards and digital wallets, Paymentology is enabling financial services in regions where traditional banking has historically failed to reach.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We are backing a mission-critical infrastructure provider,&#8221; noted Matteo Stefanel, co-founder and managing partner at Apis Partners. &#8220;Paymentology operates at the centre of an attractive, fast-growing segment, and we look forward to helping them deliver lasting impact by improving access to modern financial services worldwide.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As the company rolls out its new brand identity this week to match its expanded mission, the message to the market is clear: the future of payments is no longer tethered to the past.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/paymentology-raises-175m-to-expand-global-payments/" data-wpel-link="internal">Paymentology Raises $175M to Expand Global Payments</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
