					<description><![CDATA[<p>Adfin has raised $18 million in Series A funding. The investment will allow the firm to revolutionise business revenue collection and cashflow management through what it terms &#8216;agentic finance&#8217;, where</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/adfin-raises-18m-to-automate-finance-workflows/" data-wpel-link="internal">Adfin Raises $18M to Automate Finance Workflows</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://adfin.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Adfin </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has raised $18 million in Series A </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/ripple-prime-secures-200m-debt-deal-from-neuberger/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. The investment will allow the firm to revolutionise business revenue collection and cashflow management through what it terms &#8216;agentic finance&#8217;, where AI agents will proactively complete financial workflows, not just advise.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The whole funding round was led by Index Ventures, which backed some of the biggest industry players early on, such as Revoleu and Adyen. Support from Visionaries Club continues from the investor, and new high-profile investors joined the round, such as Stéphane Kurgan (ex-King COO) and Andrey Khusid (founder of Miro).</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the SME Late-Payment Crisis</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Adfin’s mission is centred on a persistent pain point for small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs): the late payment epidemic. In the UK, approximately 63% of invoices issued by SMEs are paid past their due dates. This delay creates a dangerous ripple effect, stifling hiring, slowing expansion, and, in extreme cases, leading to business failure due to poor liquidity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Money movement isn&#8217;t just admin; it&#8217;s the bloodstream of every company,&#8221; said Tom Pope, co-founder and CEO of Adfin. &#8220;We are building an agentic platform that automates the workflows finance teams use to get paid and manage their money, ensuring the process is safe, auditable, and firmly under human control.&#8221;</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201079" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201079" class="wp-image-201079" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Adfin.jpeg" alt="Adfin" width="400" height="400" /><p id="caption-attachment-201079" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Adfin</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Adfin differentiates itself by owning the full stack. Unlike software that simply sits on top of existing banks, Adfin combines its own proprietary payment infrastructure with intelligent AI agents. This allows the system to autonomously decide the best way to chase an invoice and then reconcile the payment instantly across accounting platforms like Xero and QuickBooks.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News:</span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/ripple-prime-secures-200m-debt-deal-from-neuberger/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400"> Ripple Prime Secures $200M Debt Deal from Neuberger</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Proven Results and Market Traction</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s impact is already reflected in its data. Businesses using Adfin report that only 9% of their invoices are paid late, a staggering improvement compared to the national average of 63%. This efficiency has helped Adfin scale rapidly to serve more than 1,500 businesses, ranging from accounting and law firms to trade professionals and care providers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors have taken note of this specialised focus. Julia André, a partner at Index Ventures, noted that the firm is tripling down on Adfin because the team has demonstrated a rare ability to obsess over a specific problem and deliver category-defining results.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Roadmap to Self-Moving Money</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With $18 million in fresh capital, Adfin plans to move beyond simple revenue collection. The company is eyeing end-to-end cash flow management, with the ultimate goal of creating a system where money moves itself. This includes automating payables, optimising cash positions, and providing predictive analytics to help business owners make better financial decisions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funds will also support a hiring surge across engineering and sales teams, as well as the groundwork for international expansion, as Adfin looks to export its automated finance model to markets outside the UK.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/adfin-raises-18m-to-automate-finance-workflows/" data-wpel-link="internal">Adfin Raises $18M to Automate Finance Workflows</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
